[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ White to play and draw. }
1. Kb3 (1. Ka3 { This also works but Kb3 brings the king toward the action immediately. }) 1... Kd4 2. Kb4 Ke3 3. Kc4 (3. Kc5 { This also works but play the less committal Kc4 for the continuation. }) 3... Kf2 { White has two drawing plans here but play Kd3 for the continuation. } 4. Kd3 Kxg2 5. Ke4 Kg3 6. Kf5 Kh4 7. Kg6 f5 8. h6 { Excellent! Pushing the h pawn prevents the f pawn from advancing and ensures that black has an h pawn rather than a g pawn. } 8... gxh6 9. Kxf5 { Excellent! White can't allow the f pawn to advance. } (9. Kxh6 { Wrong! Now white can't catch the f pawn. }) 9... Kh5 10. Kf4 { Excellent! Now white draws the game. } *


