{ White to play and win. }
1. Kg3 (1. Kg5 { White can still win but only by starting over again. }) (1. Kh3 { This works but play Kg3 for the continuation. }) 1... Kf7 2. Kf3 (2. Kg2 { This works but play Kf3 for the continuation. }) (2. Kf2 { This works but play Kf3 for the continuation. }) 2... Kf6 3. Ke4 (3. Ke3 { This works but play Ke4 for the continuation. }) (3. Kf2 { This works but play Ke4 for the continuation. }) 3... Ke6 4. g5 Kd6 5. f5 Ke7 6. f6+ { Excellent! The only move. The f pawn controls the e7 square and prevents black from maintaining an important opposition. } 6... Kf7 7. Ke5 { Excellent! The f6 pawn prevents black from taking the opposition on e7. } (7. Kd5 { This also works but play Ke5 for the continuation. }) 7... Kf8 { White has many ways to win, but which is the fastest? } 8. f7 { Excellent! } 8... Kxf7 9. Kd6 Kf8 10. Ke6 Kg7 11. Ke7 Kg8 12. Kf6 Kh7 13. Kf7 Kh8 14. Kxg6 Kg8 15. Kh6 *


