{ White has more than one idea here. What did Capablanca play against Conde in Hastings 1919? }
1. b4 axb4 2. a5 Kc7 3. g5 fxg5 4. fxg5 hxg5 5. hxg5 (5. h5 { Wrong! Black wins after b3! or g4! }) 5... b3 6. Kd3 { The only move! Black can't promote and can't defend both sides of the board. } *


