{ White's king is more active but black has two winning moves here. }
1... g5 (1... f4 { This also works but play g5 for the continuation. }) 2. exf5 g4 3. fxg4 e4 4. gxh5 { What is black's best plan here? } 4... e3 { Excellent! Black can still win with a king move, but this is the only way forward. } 5. Kd3 c4+ (5... e2 { This also wins but play c4+ for the continuation. }) 6. bxc4 b3 (6... e2 { This still wins but play b3 for the continuation. }) 7. axb3 a2 { The most direct. Black can still win after e2 but the pawn falls anyway. } *


