{ White to play and win. }
3. g4 hxg4 4. h5 Ke6 { Black's king remains inside the square of the h pawn. What does white do here? } 5. Kf2 (5. Ke2 { This also works but play Kf2 for the continuation. }) 5... Kf7 6. Kg3 (6. Kg2 { This also works but play Kg3 for the continuation. }) 6... Kg7 7. Kxg4 Kh6 8. Kf5 Kg7 9. e5 (9. Kg4 { White is still winning but this makes no progress. What's the only other winning move? }) 9... fxe5 10. Kxg5 { Excellent! And now white marches to the queenside while the black king is distracted by the h pawn. } *


[Event "Tactics in Pawn Endgames: Exercise #34"]
[Date "2023.02.11"]
