{ Black to play and win. }
1... a3 2. bxa3 { And now black can easily collect the kingside pawns and promote first. Play Kf3 for the continuation. } 2... Kf3 3. Kxa5 Kxf2 (3... h5 { This also works but play Kxf2 for the continuation. }) 4. Kb5 { It's easy to rush here, but it's important to calculate all the different promotions, because only one way works. } 4... h5 { The only move! } (4... Kg2 { Now white can draw with a4! Black needs to promote on the h1 square to guard a8, but if the king captures the h pawn then it loses a crucial tempo leaving the h file again. }) 5. a4 h4 { Only move! } 6. a5 g3 { Only move! } 7. hxg3 h3 { Excellent! Black needs to promote on h1 to guard the a8 square. } *


