{ It looks like black's king can capture the pawns and take the opposition, but white has one move to draw. What is it? }
1. g6 { The only move! By luring the black pawn forward white creates a new set of key squares which it will be able to defend. } 1... fxg6 2. f5 { The only move! } 2... gxf5 3. Kg1 { Again the only move! This allows white to control the opposition. } *


