[Event "Tactics in Pawn Endgames: Exercise #61"]
[Date "2023.02.12"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Tactics in Pawn Endgames"]
[ChapterName "Exercise #61"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/kSK7Uq54/0xQ6SfyR"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/njswift"]
[FEN "6k1/8/5P1P/8/ppp5/8/2K5/8 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2023.02.12"]
[UTCTime "16:54:28"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ White to move and win. }
1. Kb1 { The only move! White passes the move to black. From the b1 square white's king can block any pawn that advances on the queenside. } 1... a3 2. Ka2 { It's hopeless to push the pawns, so what if black tries to capture white's pawns and come into the fight? } 2... Kf7 3. h7 { Black has no way to defend the h pawn and the same would be true of the f pawn if black had tried to capture the h pawn first. The separated pawns defend each other in this way. } *


