[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2023.02.12"]
[UTCTime "16:58:34"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ White to play and draw. }
1. a4 { The only move! White moves it's pawn forward and takes away a square from the black king. } 1... a5 2. Kd3 Kb4 3. Kd4 Kxa4 4. Kc4 { The only move! White forces black's king farther away from the f pawn. The draw is only possible by preventing Kb5 amazingly. } 4... Ka3 5. Kd5 a4 6. Ke6 Kb4 7. Kxf6 a3 8. Ke7 { Excellent! If white goes to g7 then the f pawn will be pinned after black promotes. } 8... a2 9. f6 a1=Q 10. f7 { And white has a drawn queen endgame. } *


