{ Black is up a pawn but white can win this. How? }
1. Kd4 f4 2. Ke5 a5 3. a3 a4 4. Kf5 d4 5. Ke4 d3 6. Kxd3 Kd5 7. g3 { The only move! This guarantees that white can win the kingside pawns and the black king is tied to the defense of the c pawn. } 7... f3 8. g4 *


